01:09.101 --> 01:10.230
Who is he?

01:17.569 --> 01:20.070
Oh, my God. Oh, my God!

01:20.436 --> 01:23.500
Just shut up, Angela.
Let him do what he wants!

01:23.849 --> 01:25.181
-No! No!
-No!

01:25.242 --> 01:26.209
All right, go ahead.

01:28.990 --> 01:30.490
No!

01:31.640 --> 01:32.489
No!

01:33.041 --> 01:34.541
Grandpa!

01:39.014 --> 01:39.849
No!

01:42.141 --> 01:42.891
No!

01:50.459 --> 01:51.323
No!

01:55.707 --> 01:57.000
Help me!

02:09.144 --> 02:11.015
Please don't kill me.

02:17.554 --> 02:18.329
No!

02:20.555 --> 02:21.276
No!

02:23.024 --> 02:24.081
No!

02:27.433 --> 02:29.633
No!

02:43.552 --> 02:44.817
Okay, people.

02:46.715 --> 02:49.497
Now please take your time
in answering this question.

02:49.917 --> 02:52.073
I want you to take a
good look at Mr. Boffano,

02:52.134 --> 02:53.763
the man seated in front of you there.

02:54.431 --> 02:56.055
And tell me if you've
ever seen him before.

02:57.325 --> 02:58.034
No, sir, I haven't.

02:59.059 --> 03:00.174
I'm sorry I can't hear you.

03:00.256 --> 03:01.936
Would you pull the mic
a little closer, please?

03:04.099 --> 03:05.476
No, sir, I haven't.

03:05.983 --> 03:07.740
On TV? In the newspapers?

03:08.113 --> 03:08.897
No, sir.

03:09.760 --> 03:11.403
Do you read newspapers, ma'am?

03:12.441 --> 03:14.069
When I have the time.

03:14.509 --> 03:15.660
How often is that?

03:16.959 --> 03:17.686
Never.

03:19.714 --> 03:21.283
I am a single mother, Your Honour,

03:21.344 --> 03:22.919
and I am trying to be a sculptor.

03:23.043 --> 03:25.869
I have, well, a job all day

03:25.930 --> 03:27.855
and when I get home I take care of my son.

03:27.923 --> 03:31.108
I feel stupid saying that I don't
keep up with the news, but...

03:32.060 --> 03:35.040
Well, that's just how it is.
I don't. I don't have time.

03:35.230 --> 03:38.270
Ma'am, are you saying that you've
heard nothing about this case?

03:39.710 --> 03:41.114
Well, no, I have heard something.

03:41.970 --> 03:45.547
When I told my son that I might
be picked for jury duty, he said,

03:45.715 --> 03:48.118
'Hey, maybe you'll get picked
for that big Mafia case.'

03:48.179 --> 03:49.968
And I said, 'What big Mafia case?'

03:50.645 --> 03:52.287
And he said, 'You know, Louie Boffano.'

03:52.347 --> 03:54.814
'He's gonna be tried
for popping those guys.'

03:56.181 --> 03:58.380
And he said that popping
is when you kill somebody.

03:58.441 --> 03:59.467
I said, 'Okay, I've got that.

04:00.092 --> 04:01.509
But who's Louie Boffano?'

04:02.176 --> 04:04.977
And he said, 'Mom, come on,
he's the big Spaghetti O.'

04:10.198 --> 04:11.464
Okay, people.

04:12.033 --> 04:12.853
Enough!

04:13.775 --> 04:17.399
Well, ma'am, what I want you to understand
is that this may be a lengthy trial,

04:17.461 --> 04:19.766
and that you would be sequestered
during deliberations.

04:20.341 --> 04:21.583
So if you tell me

04:21.644 --> 04:24.587
that it would prove a grave hardship
for you to serve on this jury,

04:25.046 --> 04:26.208
I'll excuse you.

04:26.999 --> 04:29.124
Well, then I think I could get someone

04:29.185 --> 04:32.334
to take care of my son
for when I'm sequestered.

04:32.587 --> 04:33.941
You would like to serve?

04:36.215 --> 04:37.877
Um, yes, I would.

04:38.103 --> 04:38.680
Yes.

04:57.412 --> 04:58.057
Hey, Eddie,

04:58.389 --> 05:01.385
