11:57.832 --> 11:59.388
The Momba!

12:15.683 --> 12:16.427
Hey, Lainie.

12:16.888 --> 12:18.103
-Hey, Annie.
-Is she here?

12:18.243 --> 12:19.462
Yeah, she's coming right out.

12:31.132 --> 12:33.079
His name is Mark Cordell. He's...

12:33.697 --> 12:34.642
well, I don't know...

12:34.702 --> 12:35.969
He's very polite, but...

12:36.708 --> 12:38.713
he can be very intimidating.
You know what I mean?

12:38.773 --> 12:40.631
He knows his shit, Annie.

12:41.069 --> 12:42.883
He does Alice Aycock, Christy Rupp.

12:43.020 --> 12:45.585
He does not like
the big-dick marble cowboys.

12:46.314 --> 12:48.656
Anyway, he collects for himself,
but mostly for friends.

12:48.716 --> 12:51.459
And I mean big, big collectors,
honey, big, big shits.

12:51.519 --> 12:52.020
Like?

12:52.920 --> 12:54.620
Sato Makamoto.

12:55.690 --> 12:56.951
Bidi Karamora.

12:57.158 --> 12:58.826
My stuff's gonna go to Japan?

12:58.887 --> 13:01.005
I don't know,
just some of the names he mentioned.

13:01.396 --> 13:03.838
-Wait a minute, you didn't ask who?
-Of course I asked.

13:03.969 --> 13:05.206
He gave me vague.

13:05.327 --> 13:07.176
-And that was good enough for you?
-Well,

13:07.349 --> 13:08.324
that and a check,

13:08.767 --> 13:10.097
for $24,000.

13:11.472 --> 13:12.872
Half of which is yours.

13:15.217 --> 13:17.034
God, do I need this!

13:23.839 --> 13:24.629
Annie Laird?

13:26.191 --> 13:27.362
I thought it might be you.

13:27.422 --> 13:29.742
Inez said you might drop by
so I took a chance.

13:30.753 --> 13:32.738
I bought some of your pieces.
I'm Mark Cordell.

13:32.894 --> 13:34.011
-Hi.
-Hi.

13:34.099 --> 13:36.069
I've got a check in my bag. Thank you.

13:36.130 --> 13:37.754
Well, I didn't pay you
nearly what they're worth.

13:37.916 --> 13:39.428
No. Please, please.

13:40.603 --> 13:43.182
How do you know me? Have we met before?

13:43.340 --> 13:45.172
Inez showed me your
picture in the catalogue.

13:45.699 --> 13:46.575
Oh, God.

13:48.052 --> 13:49.799
Well, you know, she said that my...

13:50.011 --> 13:52.413
pieces were gonna go to Japan.
Is that true?

13:52.504 --> 13:54.279
-Yeah, that's likely.
-So does that mean that's it?

13:54.348 --> 13:55.656
I'm not gonna see them again.

13:55.716 --> 13:56.749
No, not necessarily. No.

13:57.218 --> 13:59.952
Do you have some time to talk this over?
Maybe have some lunch?

14:00.304 --> 14:01.843
Oh, now? You know, I'm...

14:02.755 --> 14:05.855
supposed to be upstate
by 2:00 for jury duty.

14:07.929 --> 14:09.493
Well, I wouldn't wanna
make you late for that.

14:11.299 --> 14:12.427
Well, maybe just a quick bite.

14:14.302 --> 14:15.091
So what was the first one?

14:16.270 --> 14:18.270
Okay, the first one. Let me see...

14:20.696 --> 14:21.941
The very first one.

14:22.610 --> 14:23.878
When my parents split-up,

14:24.679 --> 14:27.019
I went to stay with my
grandmother for the summer

14:27.080 --> 14:29.245
in Allentown, Pennsylvania. I hated it.

14:29.960 --> 14:32.213
So I made this model of a wild meadow.

14:32.687 --> 14:34.990
And I would keep it under the bed.

14:35.623 --> 14:38.971
It had these bushes.
It had thorns that I made out of staples,

14:39.032 --> 14:41.290
and there was a stream
made out of tin foil.

14:42.130 --> 14:43.215
And I would...

14:43.676 --> 14:44.841
reach under the bed,

14:45.633 --> 14:47.630
you know, 'cause I was afraid of the dark,

14:48.436 --> 14:50.028
and I would reach under and...

14:50.383 --> 14:51.429
just touch it

14:53.238 --> 14:54.369
and dream I was there.

14:57.078 --> 14:58.210
And that's how you got started?

14:59.002 --> 14:59.592
Yeah.

15:00.081 --> 15:01.142
So what about you?

15:01.673 --> 15:03.008
Were you afraid of the dark?

15:04.745 --> 15:06.708
Well, it wasn't really very much dark...

15:07.703 --> 15:09.776
in my house. We had a lot of kids.

15:10.113 --> 15:11.116
I was the youngest.

15:13.828 --> 15:15.120
A real madhouse,

15:16.846 --> 15:17.518
a zoo.

15:19.233 --> 15:20.006
Anyway,

15:21.003 --> 15:22.225
you wanna know...

15:22.358 --> 15:24.240
where your pieces are going, yes?

15:24.301 --> 15:24.951
Mmm-hmm.

15:25.491 --> 15:26.858
-Do you know Japan?
-Mmm-mmm.

15:27.180 --> 15:29.923
Well, contemporary art is a
sort of currency there now

15:29.984 --> 15:31.354
because its...

15:31.588 --> 15:33.196
value is so inconstant.

15:33.274 --> 15:34.021
It's so...

15:34.417 --> 15:35.573
attractively pliant.

15:35.650 --> 15:36.787
Wait a second. I'm...

15:36.980 --> 15:38.395
I'm... I'm... I'm lost.

15:40.748 --> 15:43.839
-I'm not connecting the dots here.
-None of that really matters.

15:43.972 --> 15:46.352
All that really matter is that we
need to start getting new pieces,

15:46.413 --> 15:49.187
try to record some six figure sales,

15:49.248 --> 15:51.256
get you the right review in Artforum,

15:51.365 --> 15:53.452
a proper niche at the Basel Art Fair.

15:53.513 --> 15:56.113
