You mean 'sleep' sleep?

17:36.771 --> 17:39.451
Not just closing my eyes for a second
while I'm doing a tracheotomy?

17:41.673 --> 17:43.719
I don't know. I slept for a
couple of hours on Monday night.

17:44.321 --> 17:46.041
-Jesus! Why aren't you at home, in bed?
-Would you cut it out?

17:46.102 --> 17:48.801
I'm going to take the kids to a movie.
This is a cinch.

17:49.050 --> 17:49.593
Annie?

17:50.017 --> 17:50.734
What?

17:51.531 --> 17:52.671
How could I not come?

17:55.072 --> 17:57.747
This thing today was the triumph
of your life, girlfriend.

17:59.775 --> 18:00.502
What?

18:02.930 --> 18:05.423
# You, you You did it #

18:07.601 --> 18:08.677
What did I do?

18:09.528 --> 18:11.985
You sold three goddamn pieces!

18:12.773 --> 18:13.706
You know what? I did!

18:19.322 --> 18:22.690
Laozi says that returning
is the movement of the Dao.

18:24.218 --> 18:25.343
So are you a Daoist?

18:26.207 --> 18:27.177
I don't know.

18:29.357 --> 18:32.066
Laozi says that when the foolish
man first hears of the Dao,

18:32.126 --> 18:33.301
he laughs out loud,

18:33.361 --> 18:35.214
which is certainly true
in my case, I'm afraid,

18:35.496 --> 18:37.712
but I also find it very compelling.

18:38.699 --> 18:42.276
Become a valley,
stop fighting against that structure

18:42.336 --> 18:44.939
against that fate, what have you,

18:45.992 --> 18:48.927
and everything will flow to you.

18:53.948 --> 18:54.948
What do you think?

18:56.984 --> 18:58.323
I think we need to take a left.

19:07.862 --> 19:10.396
-Should I just...
-Yeah, any one. It doesn't matter.

19:12.233 --> 19:13.541
Just like the ones in the gallery.

19:13.601 --> 19:15.600
You just stick your hand under and...

19:15.661 --> 19:16.989
Cop a feel, yeah.

19:21.142 --> 19:23.471
'The Dream of Giving Notice.'

19:35.046 --> 19:35.821
Hmm.

19:38.007 --> 19:39.188
What do you feel?

19:39.920 --> 19:40.920
A keyboard.

19:43.033 --> 19:46.761
A computer keyboard and
something rough on the keys.

19:46.822 --> 19:47.854
Is it sandpaper?

19:49.837 --> 19:50.911
This is...

19:50.971 --> 19:52.905
What is this? This is wire.

19:54.008 --> 19:55.430
This is a cage.

19:57.244 --> 19:58.527
This is a birdcage.

20:00.581 --> 20:02.548
I'm caught in a birdcage.

20:05.920 --> 20:07.290
The door is open, but I can't

20:08.272 --> 20:09.827
quite squeeze through.

20:12.470 --> 20:17.070
And now I feel a breeze on my
fingertips just beyond my reach.

20:17.131 --> 20:18.275
How did you do that?

20:22.565 --> 20:23.862
And now a fluttering...

20:26.207 --> 20:27.253
This is a bird.

20:29.080 --> 20:30.273
This is amazing.

20:32.877 --> 20:35.258
This is also a little bit strange. I mean,

20:35.660 --> 20:38.567
reaching up underneath
here and feeling your...

20:39.887 --> 20:40.887
Private stuff?

20:42.256 --> 20:43.143
Private stuff.

20:46.123 --> 20:47.145
My God!

20:48.128 --> 20:52.877
Annie, it doesn't have to only be a dream.
You can give notice.

20:53.200 --> 20:54.978
You can escape that hell.

20:55.228 --> 20:59.320
You can do nothing but just make
art for the rest of your life.

21:12.934 --> 21:14.302
Would you like to feel another one?

21:15.022 --> 21:17.376
There's a really good one
right over there.

21:27.839 --> 21:29.572
-This one?
-Yeah, that one.

21:31.633 --> 21:33.551
But I've already felt that one.

21:35.047 --> 21:37.648
No, no. That one's the one...
I just finished that one.

21:38.984 --> 21:40.843
Well, I felt it yesterday.

21:43.365 --> 21:45.085
Yesterday? I didn't even
know you yesterday.

21:47.406 --> 21:48.316
But I was here.

21:54.628 --> 21:55.647
You're kidding, right?

22:12.662 --> 22:13.340
Don't get up.

22:19.286 --> 22:20.716
Annie, listen to me now.

22:23.057 --> 22:25.799
You're in danger
and your son is in danger.

22:25.859 --> 22:27.339
Oliver. What do you mean? Where's my son?

22:27.417 --> 22:29.697
He went with Jesse and Juliet
to the movies, didn't he?

22:31.098 --> 22:32.377
He's gonna be all right.

22:34.268 --> 22:36.207
Such an extraordinary child.

22:36.968 --> 22:37.757
Remember last night,

22:37.818 --> 22:39.792
when the two of you were playing
that video game upstairs

22:39.853 --> 22:41.818
and you started to panic and he said,
'Chill out, Momba.'

22:41.918 --> 22:42.701
You remember that?

22:45.131 --> 22:46.197
How do you know that?

22:47.335 --> 22:48.036
Annie,

22:50.368 --> 22:53.517
when I heard the two of you,
together, laughing,

22:53.654 --> 22:55.930
I swore to myself
that I would do everything

22:55.990 --> 22:58.299
to make sure that he gets through this.

22:58.713 --> 22:59.900
Do you understand me, Annie?

22:59.960 --> 23:03.184
This is a very dangerous time for him.

23:03.766 --> 23:05.427
He could stray.

23:06.033 --> 23:09.468
He could commit some childish
error and we could lose him.

23:10.141 --> 23:10.797
That quick.

23:16.477 --> 23:17.324
But you know what I think?

23:18.545 --> 23:19.891
I think he's gonna be safe.

23:20.207 --> 23:22.219
I think he'll grow up
and he'll be healthy.

23:23.074 --> 23:25.740
And your friend, Juliet, she'll
be safe too. She'll be fine.

23:26.075 --> 23:29.820
Everyone you care about,
they'll all be safe as churches.

23:30.005 --> 23:31.083
Do you hear what I'm saying?

23:31.792 --> 23:32.403
Annie,

23:33.692 --> 23:35.481
nod your head now. Do as I say.

23:40.543 --> 23:41.805
And, as for you,

23:44.638 --> 23:46.027
all you have to do is wait.

23:47.634 --> 23:48.502
That's all.

23:48.965 --> 23:51.524
And then someone is going to contact you,

23:52.133 --> 23:54.554
and tell you to say two words.

23:54.877 --> 23:56.738
Two precisely.

23:57.334 --> 23:59.214
Do you know what they are?
Have you guessed yet?

24:00.533 --> 24:01.185
No.

24:06.794 --> 24:08.960
Not guilty.

24:26.800 --> 24:28.099
Okay, Annie's home.

24:31.085 --> 24:34.151
-Okay, brat, see you later.
-Okay, I'll see you later.

24:34.212 --> 24:35.126
Get out of here.

24:35.323 --> 24:36.471
What do you want me to do?

24:40.060 --> 24:40.879
Protect him.

24:43.897 --> 24:46.051
Tell him that your date
turned out to be a creep.

24:51.572 --> 24:52.215
Hey.

24:52.657 --> 24:53.881
Hi there.

24:54.842 --> 24:56.708
-Hey, you all right?
-Yeah.

24:57.845 --> 24:59.344
Oh, it's nice to see you.

25:01.715 --> 25:03.126
-What's the matter?
-Nothing.

25:03.187 --> 25:04.962
-Did you have a good time?
-Yeah.

25:05.152 --> 25:06.862
-So what's the matter?
-Nothing, nothing.

25:07.488 --> 25:09.716
Things just didn't go great with that guy.

25:10.772 --> 25:12.942
-Is he still gonna buy your boxes?
-Doesn't matter.

25:15.252 --> 25:16.802
-Here.
-You okay?

25:16.863 --> 25:18.351
I am fine, sweetie. Go.

25:18.766 --> 25:20.011
I'll be up in a minute, all right.

25:21.969 --> 25:22.809
Just go on.

25:36.621 --> 25:38.196
I still wanna buy your boxes.

25:38.257 --> 25:40.032
No, I don't want you to buy my boxes.

25:40.287 --> 25:41.150
I insist.

25:42.062 --> 25:44.295
Annie, this will be over
before you know it.

26:14.822 --> 26:15.381
What?

26:15.647 --> 26:17.716
Annie. Hey, what's up?

26:18.820 --> 26:19.500
Boone?

26:19.560 --> 26:20.968
Yeah, it's me.

26:21.028 --> 26:22.536
Oh, Jesus. How are you?

26:22.596 --> 26:24.382
I'm good. How the hell are you?

26:24.498 --> 26:25.706
Hey, listen, don't go anywhere,

26:25.766 --> 26:27.297
I've to put money in the phone, okay?

26:27.803 --> 26:30.019
It's the 1950s here. Don't do anything.

26:30.080 --> 26:31.332
It's gonna sound like we're disconnected.

26:31.393 --> 26:32.237
Are you there?

26:32.506 --> 26:33.533
Yes, that's better.

26:33.594 --> 26:36.215
So, I brought one of the kids
down to the hospital today,

26:36.276 --> 26:38.252
and I just thought I'd
grab a chance to call you.

26:38.312 --> 26:40.120
How long has it been?
How long since we talked?

26:40.180 --> 26:43.267
Well, I don't know, probably the fall,
sometime in the fall.

26:43.534 --> 26:44.615
No, has it been...

26:45.440 --> 26:47.528
It's been that long. You
know, I've meaning to call,

26:47.697 --> 26:50.430
but I'm still three hours
from the nearest phone.

26:50.490 --> 26:51.578
It's just not that easy.

26:51.639 --> 26:53.674
How are you guys anyway? How's Oliver?

26:56.515 --> 26:58.782
-Annie? Are you there? Yeah?
-Um...

27:00.267 --> 27:01.480
Yeah,

27:02.730 --> 27:03.544
we're okay.

27:03.604 --> 27:04.878
Good. I thought I lost you.

27:04.938 --> 27:08.615
Listen, Annie,
book your airline early this time, okay?

27:08.675 --> 27:10.063
Because last time you know what happened.

27:10.124 --> 27:12.052
You know, I don't think we'll be able
to make it this summer. I'm sorry.

27:12.112 --> 27:13.404
You're not gonna make it?

27:13.465 --> 27:15.675
-Annie, you'll miss the fiesta. Why?
-Boone,

27:16.937 --> 27:19.770
you know, just because
we had a connection once,

27:19.831 --> 27:20.933
about a million years ago,

27:20.994 --> 27:23.136
doesn't mean that you can just
keep popping up into my life

27:23.197 --> 27:23.926
whenever you want.

27:24.371 --> 27:25.507
Annie, what's the matter?

27:26.101 --> 27:29.445
I have someone here and he
doesn't like these phone calls,

27:29.630 --> 27:30.967
and, frankly, neither do I.

27:31.819 --> 27:32.908
Okay. Uh...

27:34.701 --> 27:36.476
Sorry. I didn't know.

27:36.536 --> 27:37.397
You okay?

27:38.140 --> 27:41.241
Yeah. And I'll be great when
I can just get back to sleep.

27:57.076 --> 27:58.209
Good night, Annie.

28:09.202 --> 28:11.311
I'm talking to the Teacher
and he says to me,

28:11.371 --> 28:14.375
'Man don't want to come out of his house.
Man don't want to be killed.'

28:14.672 --> 28:15.403
So what?

28:16.206 --> 28:17.598
So we could dig a tunnel.

28:18.209 --> 28:19.343
You remember what he said to me, Paulie?

28:19.404 --> 28:20.871
I remember, Louie. I remember.

28:20.932 --> 28:24.660
And I say to the Teacher, I say,
'You wanna dig a tunnel?'

28:24.721 --> 28:28.546
'Okay, dig a tunnel.
Just kill that cocksucker.'

28:30.598 --> 28:31.840
Mr. DeCicco,

28:31.972 --> 28:33.786
that is you on the
prosecutions tape, isn't it?

28:33.847 --> 28:34.411
Yeah.

28:34.588 --> 28:37.400
It's you and Louie Boffano
talking about the Teacher.

28:37.885 --> 28:38.581
Yeah.

28:38.699 --> 28:39.931
So, who is this Teacher?

28:41.513 --> 28:42.091
I don't know.

28:42.152 --> 28:44.501
Do you know why he's called the Teacher,
Mr. DeCicco?

28:45.220 --> 28:46.649
'Cause when you see him, school's out.

28:50.010 --> 28:50.941
School's out.

28:51.421 --> 28:52.090
Meaning?

28:53.194 --> 28:54.464
What the fuck you think it means?

28:54.783 --> 28:55.708
Means you're dead.

28:56.173 --> 28:58.479
Mr. DeCicco, not here.

28:59.852 --> 29:00.187
-Sorry.

29:00.295 --> 29:02.415
Did you have any direct
dealings with this Teacher?

29:02.872 --> 29:05.314
No, nobody knows who he is.
He just does special jobs for Louie.

29:05.662 --> 29:08.301
But didn't you testify
yesterday under directive

29:08.362 --> 29:10.536
that the Teacher had suggested a strategy

29:10.597 --> 29:12.369
for negotiating with the Cali Drug Cartel.

29:12.899 --> 29:14.608
-Maybe, but he didn't...
-It was the Teacher

29:14.668 --> 29:18.075
who arranged the link between Louie
and the Calabrian Mafia, wasn't it?

29:19.071 --> 29:19.611
Yeah.

29:19.905 --> 29:22.664
Two alliances Salvador
Riggio bitterly opposed.

29:23.698 --> 29:24.268
Yeah.

29:24.543 --> 29:26.042
And then one day the Teacher said

29:26.103 --> 29:28.364
he could dig a tunnel to the
house of Salvador Riggio

29:28.425 --> 29:29.882
for the purpose of killing him, right?

29:30.905 --> 29:31.441
-Right.

29:31.714 --> 29:33.129
-And Louie Boffano said,

29:33.469 --> 29:34.619
'You wanna dig a tunnel.

29:34.959 --> 29:36.217
Okay, dig a tunnel.'

29:37.108 --> 29:37.600
Yeah.

29:38.076 --> 29:39.924
After all, the Teacher is the boss.

29:39.985 --> 29:41.044
He can do what he wants, right?

29:41.336 --> 29:43.690
Come on, give me a break.
Teacher's not the boss.

29:44.131 --> 29:45.981
You know of a single case
in which his counsel

29:46.042 --> 29:47.852
wasn't followed, Mr. DeCicco?

29:48.268 --> 29:50.944
I told you, Louie's the boss.
Louie gives the orders.

29:51.004 --> 29:54.328
You mean Louie seems
to give the orders, right?

29:54.769 --> 29:58.258
Mr. DeCicco, do you know what a puppet is?

29:58.319 --> 29:59.987
-Objection, Your Honour.
-Sustained.

30:00.047 --> 30:01.527
I'm sorry. Let me put it another way.

30:02.616 --> 30:03.825
This is a puppet.

30:04.451 --> 30:06.469
Maybe it seems to make its own decisions.

30:06.530 --> 30:07.734
Objection.

30:07.795 --> 30:09.460
Sustained. Mr. Bozeman,
this is not a circus.

30:09.575 --> 30:10.809
I withdraw the puppet.

30:10.981 --> 30:12.122
No further questions.

30:12.190 --> 30:14.133
The reporter will strike
that remark from the record.

30:14.194 --> 30:15.609
The jury will disregard it.

30:15.704 --> 30:18.704
Counsel, take that puppet and put it away.

30:18.765 --> 30:20.431
I just sustained an objection to it.

30:40.654 --> 30:41.586
Oliver?

30:42.767 --> 30:44.542
-Oliver?
-Yeah.

30:44.891 --> 30:46.423
Please get down here.

30:46.660 --> 30:47.757
Anybody here?

30:48.462 --> 30:50.281
-I was just playing around.
-Yeah, well,

30:50.664 --> 30:54.521
just take your costume off the kitchen
table and put it where it belongs.

30:55.735 --> 30:56.612
Mom...

30:56.815 --> 30:58.523
-Oliver...
-It was a joke.

30:58.638 --> 31:00.848
Well, I'm not the mood, okay?

31:05.946 --> 31:07.503
-What is it, Oliver?
-Mom...

31:17.023 --> 31:17.851
What is this?

31:18.291 --> 31:20.868
This is my math...

31:38.912 --> 31:41.888
You should just say something.
Even if it's just, 'Okay.'

31:41.948 --> 31:44.391
I got a 37 out of 100.

31:44.451 --> 31:46.617
I can see that.
What do you want me to say?

31:47.998 --> 31:49.151
What's this?

32:04.974 --> 32:06.830
I thought I told you never to come here.

32:08.103 --> 32:08.895
Well, I...

32:09.722 --> 32:11.172
You know, I need some help.

32:11.673 --> 32:14.709
Could I get a few bucks
on next month's rent? Huh?

32:14.770 --> 32:16.892
-What the fuck is this?
-Don't touch that!

32:21.535 --> 32:22.683
It's a piece of art.

32:23.404 --> 32:26.553
Rodney, it's a very delicate piece of art.

32:28.253 --> 32:30.770
There you go.
Here's somebody you have got to meet.

32:30.830 --> 32:32.749
You have got to meet Lorraine.

32:33.200 --> 32:34.766
This stuff isn't hard for you.

32:37.054 --> 32:38.442
Lorraine? Who's Lorraine?

32:39.526 --> 32:40.438
My girlfriend.

32:41.283 --> 32:42.878
What's this? More art?

32:46.744 --> 32:48.202
That's my girlfriend.

32:49.054 --> 32:51.177
And, yeah, it's a piece of art.
These are all...

32:52.061 --> 32:56.221
pieces of art. That's why I didn't want you
dropping by unexpectedly because I'm...

32:58.132 --> 33:00.267
working on some very important pieces.

33:00.327 --> 33:01.902
...who you are? What you do?

33:01.962 --> 33:03.528
Let me tell you this. Get the...

33:04.698 --> 33:05.674
Rodney?

33:07.497 --> 33:07.950
Yeah.

33:08.558 --> 33:10.296
Yeah, yeah. I'll see you later.

33:10.904 --> 33:12.316
Going to do better.

33:12.689 --> 33:14.906
You know, you've said that before.

33:16.329 --> 33:18.638
-Well, I mean it this time.
-Yeah, right.

33:18.699 --> 33:21.142
You know what?
I don't want to discuss this, okay?

33:24.184 --> 33:26.083
Just get your coat on and let's go.

33:26.686 --> 33:28.239
We don't have anything
to eat in this house.

33:45.105 --> 33:46.018
Hey, I know you.

33:47.125 --> 33:48.061
You're the..

33:48.441 --> 33:49.323
the artist, right?

33:49.689 --> 33:50.383
Box lady?

33:50.889 --> 33:53.013
Buddy of mine, Mark Cordell,
bought a couple of your pieces.

33:54.551 --> 33:55.437
This your kid?

33:57.435 --> 33:59.402
-Hey, how you doing? Nice to meet you.
-Hi.

34:01.588 --> 34:03.300
What were those frozen
things that you like?

34:05.348 --> 34:07.261
-You mean RoboPops?
-Yeah, go get some.

34:14.533 --> 34:16.312
Tomorrow morning, 7:00 a.m.

34:16.813 --> 34:18.121
The park and ride in Banktree.

34:18.338 --> 34:20.121
It's off I-684, you know it?

34:20.966 --> 34:21.581
Yes.

34:23.842 --> 34:24.755
What did I say?

34:25.779 --> 34:27.745
The park and ride, 684, in Banktree.

34:28.888 --> 34:29.688
What time?

34:29.748 --> 34:30.675
7:00 a.m.

34:32.422 --> 34:33.222
Look,

34:34.949 --> 34:35.728
you'll be fine.

34:36.889 --> 34:38.092
We're not animals.

34:38.746 --> 34:40.668
I got a kid, too, just a
little older than him.

34:41.428 --> 34:42.194
Teenager.

34:45.063 --> 34:47.371
Anyway, I just want to tell you I know
what you're going through, and...

34:47.797 --> 34:48.576
hang in there.

34:52.739 --> 34:53.346
Hey!

34:55.884 --> 34:56.641
What's your name?

35:02.748 --> 35:04.014
I can't tell you my name.

35:05.121 --> 35:06.239
What do I call you then?

35:07.654 --> 35:09.008
Call me Cap'n Crunch.

35:10.974 --> 35:11.743
Captain,

35:12.412 --> 35:13.158
thanks.

35:18.398 --> 35:19.774
How are you holding up, Annie?

35:21.401 --> 35:22.847
How have you been feeling lately?

35:24.489 --> 35:27.132
Why don't you tell me?
You listen to every word we say.

35:27.474 --> 35:29.340
I don't enjoy invading your privacy.

35:30.440 --> 35:31.193
You don't?

35:32.411 --> 35:32.982
No.

35:35.782 --> 35:38.532
But we can't afford the slightest error.

35:39.351 --> 35:41.427
Now, I'm gonna say something to
you that might be unwelcome,

35:41.488 --> 35:42.887
but I'm gonna say it nonetheless,

35:42.948 --> 35:44.842
I think you're being a little
harsh with your child.

35:46.659 --> 35:49.836
He may start to ask questions.
He may talk to his friends.

35:49.896 --> 35:50.995
He won't. He won't.

35:53.800 --> 35:57.800
I just want to finish this as quickly
and as painlessly as possible,

35:58.371 --> 36:00.310
but I'm gonna need your help.

36:01.354 --> 36:02.926
We have to work together, Annie.

36:03.952 --> 36:05.652
I'll do what I can, all right?

36:09.394 --> 36:11.911
Do you understand what our strategy
was in the courtroom yesterday?

36:11.972 --> 36:13.540
What was our strategy yesterday?

36:14.821 --> 36:16.563
Louie Boffano didn't order the killing.

36:16.623 --> 36:20.200
He's in the mob, maybe a bad guy,
but just a figurehead.

36:20.260 --> 36:21.350
He doesn't give orders.

36:22.828 --> 36:23.497
That's right.

36:24.932 --> 36:26.878
And if Louie Boffano isn't guilty,

36:27.685 --> 36:28.636
then who is?

36:29.038 --> 36:30.756
Who did kill Salvador Riggio?

36:34.516 --> 36:35.174
You did.

36:44.184 --> 36:45.950
You think I'm the Teacher, Annie?

36:48.188 --> 36:49.041
Aren't you?

36:52.058 --> 36:53.434
I would have you believe that.

36:56.285 --> 36:58.248
The Teacher scares you, doesn't he, Annie?

37:00.400 --> 37:01.875
Well, I'm sorry for the fear.

37:01.935 --> 37:03.295
If I had any choice...

37:05.238 --> 37:06.352
Any choice...

37:07.540 --> 37:08.106
But

37:11.344 --> 37:12.718
if I can keep you scared,

37:14.113 --> 37:15.423
I can save your life.

37:20.565 --> 37:23.609
Then he got down on the bed
between my husband and me.

37:23.924 --> 37:26.739
And he put his gun on Sal, on his mouth.

37:27.079 --> 37:29.277
And what did the man do then, Mrs. Riggio?

37:29.338 --> 37:31.905
He said, 'Open up, Sal,
I don't wanna make a mess.'

37:32.355 --> 37:33.654
'I don't wanna scare your wife.'

37:34.780 --> 37:36.542
'We gotta work together, Sal.'

37:37.690 --> 37:38.359
And then?

37:38.692 --> 37:39.917
Then he killed my husband.

37:40.356 --> 37:41.922
He killed my Sal. Shot him.

37:43.877 --> 37:45.214
And what happened next?

37:45.678 --> 37:47.812
Then the door opened and my...

37:51.684 --> 37:52.529
Mrs. Riggio,

37:53.670 --> 37:55.114
did someone come in?

37:57.605 --> 37:58.223
Tommy,

37:59.897 --> 38:00.832
my grandson.

38:01.609 --> 38:02.641
He came in the room,

38:03.897 --> 38:05.538
and he saw my Sal dead.

38:05.699 --> 38:06.738
And then what happened?

38:07.367 --> 38:08.226
Then the man,

38:09.054 --> 38:10.054
he saw my baby.

38:10.904 --> 38:13.179
And Tommy ran away, he ran down the hall.

38:13.239 --> 38:14.461
He ran after him.

38:16.943 --> 38:18.288
Then I heard the shot.

38:20.346 --> 38:21.922
He killed my baby!

38:30.744 --> 38:31.909
No further questions.

38:46.906 --> 38:48.471
-Oliver?
-Yeah.

38:49.409 --> 38:51.318
Mom, Juliet called again.

38:51.477 --> 38:53.023
It's only, like, the tenth time.

38:55.081 --> 38:56.055
What's he doing here?

38:56.602 --> 38:57.724
What do you mean? Jesse?

38:57.784 --> 38:58.983
You're supposed to be doing your homework.

38:59.452 --> 39:00.442
Bye, Jesse.

39:01.020 --> 39:02.015
See you later.

39:03.666 --> 39:05.896
Who the hell has been
cutting into the newspaper?

39:07.088 --> 39:07.791
I did.

39:08.135 --> 39:09.326
You told me to.

39:10.773 --> 39:12.704
You know what?
You never do anything that I ask you to.

39:12.765 --> 39:14.310
Why the hell did you have to do this?

39:15.234 --> 39:16.424
'Cause you told me to!

39:18.137 --> 39:19.095
What did it say?

39:19.505 --> 39:21.143
You're not supposed to know what it says.

39:22.075 --> 39:25.095
You said you weren't supposed to
know what's in the paper or on TV.

39:25.911 --> 39:26.763
That's not right.

39:27.880 --> 39:30.573
You don't tell me what's right and wrong,
you got it?

39:31.088 --> 39:33.526
-Now, what the hell did it say?
-I don't know.

39:33.671 --> 39:35.307
Well, did it say Boffano was guilty?

39:36.293 --> 39:38.135
-I don't know!
-What did it say?

39:38.196 --> 39:40.632
Was it compelling evidence,
persuasive evidence,

39:40.693 --> 39:42.150
do they want you to think he's guilty?

39:42.211 --> 39:43.859
Mom, everybody knows he's guilty.

39:44.664 --> 39:45.551
What's the matter?

39:48.501 --> 39:49.909
What do you mean everybody?

39:50.436 --> 39:51.678
Who the hell have you been talking to?

39:51.738 --> 39:53.310
Nobody. You asked me not to.

39:53.371 --> 39:55.413
No. I am not asking you, I am telling you.

39:55.474 --> 39:56.916
You talk to anybody about this trial,

39:56.977 --> 39:59.331
and I swear to God,
I will beat the shit out of you.

39:59.612 --> 40:00.947
Do you understand me?

40:01.395 --> 40:02.174
Do you?

40:02.434 --> 40:03.134
Yeah.

40:05.823 --> 40:08.814
And that bullshit crybaby
stuff stops right now!

40:14.994 --> 40:15.880
Oh, shit.

40:19.092 --> 40:19.872
Oh, I can't...

40:20.740 --> 40:21.815
I can't do this.

40:32.879 --> 40:34.599
Where is everybody? Huh?

40:35.074 --> 40:37.374
Did I get this wrong again? Oh, jeez.

40:39.152 --> 40:40.964
What do you mean?
What time are you supposed to be here?

40:41.244 --> 40:42.822
I was supposed to be here now.

40:45.194 --> 40:48.504
You know what? I'm gonna go see if they're
in the old practice fields. Hold on.

40:48.728 --> 40:50.203
-Oliver!
-Just hold on!

40:50.263 --> 40:53.106
Get back here!
Oliver, I don't want you going!

40:53.212 --> 40:54.212
Just stay there!

40:58.283 --> 40:59.162
Hey.

41:00.652 --> 41:01.490
We need to talk.

41:01.788 --> 41:04.767
I have to go. I'm gonna be late. And I...

41:04.992 --> 41:05.665
Walk with me.

41:06.308 --> 41:08.168
-I can't.
-What if I were in trouble?

41:09.949 --> 41:11.502
-What kind of trouble?
-What if I...

41:12.502 --> 41:13.791
were in really bad trouble?

41:14.574 --> 41:17.417
What is it? Like a man, or work?
What is it?

41:17.797 --> 41:19.093
What if I couldn't tell you?

41:19.726 --> 41:20.867
What do you mean,
'If you couldn't tell me?'

41:20.927 --> 41:23.024
I'm your best friend.
You've got to tell me.

41:23.171 --> 41:25.182
-So you would tell me?
-Of course.

41:26.065 --> 41:26.874
Then do that.

41:31.086 --> 41:33.530
I can't tell you what to do,
Annie, I don't have a kid.

41:34.183 --> 41:36.750
Still you love him. You
love him as much as I do.

41:36.879 --> 41:37.688
Don't you?

41:38.311 --> 41:40.044
Tell me what to do, Juliet.

41:42.527 --> 41:44.050
I think you've got to go to the judge.

41:45.076 --> 41:46.295
You're gonna go to the judge,

41:47.403 --> 41:49.318
you're gonna tell him
that your son got sick.

41:50.823 --> 41:52.932
Tell him that your son just
got diagnosed with leukaemia.

41:52.976 --> 41:54.883
-He's not gonna buy that.
-Yeah, he will.

41:57.035 --> 41:58.723
If you have a note from your doctor.

41:59.559 --> 42:00.316
From me.

42:00.812 --> 42:01.514
Okay?

42:04.540 --> 42:05.700
I don't know.

42:07.874 --> 42:09.673
I don't know. It just...

42:10.000 --> 42:11.397
sounds sort of crazy.

42:11.458 --> 42:13.684
You're right. What you're doing,
the way you're handling it,

42:13.745 --> 42:15.754
going along with these guys.
It's much smarter.

42:16.449 --> 42:19.336
-Then why did you...
-Because I don't take orders very well.

42:20.453 --> 42:22.971
From monsters, I don't take them at all.
But that's just me.

42:24.937 --> 42:25.937
He's your kid, Annie.

42:39.906 --> 42:41.093
Once we're back in the car,

42:41.874 --> 42:43.342
you never talk about this.

42:43.661 --> 42:44.269
Okay?

42:45.107 --> 42:46.782
Not a word, not a question.

42:47.046 --> 42:49.167
Say it. Say, 'I'll never
talk about this in the car.'

42:51.258 --> 42:52.791
I'll never talk about this in the car.

42:52.852 --> 42:53.744
'Or in the house.'

42:54.554 --> 42:55.585
Or in the house.

42:59.058 --> 42:59.878
I knew it.

43:00.426 --> 43:01.911
-Oh, God.
-You're just too smart.

43:05.865 --> 43:07.507
I'm glad you figured it out.

43:09.436 --> 43:11.526
And I'm glad you went to Juliet.

43:13.673 --> 43:14.512
Are you scared?

43:15.512 --> 43:16.061
Yeah.

43:16.340 --> 43:17.405
Just a little.

43:18.778 --> 43:20.999
But we're gonna turn this thing around,
okay?

43:21.236 --> 43:21.951
Yeah.

43:44.037 --> 43:45.818
Excuse me, may I help you?

43:46.627 --> 43:48.854
I just need to see the judge.

43:53.880 --> 43:55.102
What are you doing here?

43:56.100 --> 43:57.169
I need to see you.

43:58.493 --> 43:59.638
You know who I am.

44:00.286 --> 44:01.668
Yes, you're a juror.

44:01.821 --> 44:03.049
Open that door, please.

44:03.110 --> 44:04.955
I wanna talk to you alone.

44:05.297 --> 44:07.653
Let me just explain something to you.

44:08.173 --> 44:11.182
When you come into my chambers,
this is not a trivial thing.

44:11.864 --> 44:13.588
When a juror visits a judge,

44:14.133 --> 44:16.084
this can have serious consequences.

44:17.734 --> 44:18.664
Now,

44:19.640 --> 44:21.851
if you still have a problem and you...

44:22.220 --> 44:23.677
wanna talk about it,

44:24.150 --> 44:26.651
then I'll call the Defence Attorney and
the DA and we'll sit down and talk...

44:26.712 --> 44:28.432
No, I wanna talk to you alone.

44:28.493 --> 44:31.245
I don't want them.
I only wanna talk to you.

44:32.518 --> 44:34.266
-Alone?
-Alone.

44:34.520 --> 44:36.896
Well, you can't talk to me
alone and whatever that is,

44:36.956 --> 44:39.508
I don't wanna see it.
Not without the attorneys present.

44:45.246 --> 44:47.131
Are you telling me
that I'm making a mistake?

44:51.354 --> 44:51.843
Madam,

44:52.675 --> 44:54.557
what I remember about you

44:54.799 --> 44:56.759
is that I gave you every opportunity

44:56.820 --> 44:58.705
to get out of serving on this jury.

44:59.045 --> 45:00.146
But you insisted

45:00.290 --> 45:02.677
you wanted jury duty. Do you recall?

45:03.576 --> 45:06.186
Well, you want to serve,
you don't want to serve.

45:06.419 --> 45:07.468
You have a problem,

45:07.529 --> 45:10.008
but you don't think the defendant
has a right to hear it.

45:10.856 --> 45:11.683
Well, I think

45:12.091 --> 45:12.965
you're wrong.

45:13.859 --> 45:16.159
He happens to be on trial for murder.

45:17.306 --> 45:19.141
He was every right to hear it.

45:20.032 --> 45:20.770
Now,

45:23.736 --> 45:25.287
shall I try to locate his counsel?

45:25.805 --> 45:26.439
No,

45:27.199 --> 45:28.399
I've changed my mind.

46:08.300 --> 46:10.842
You and your fucking '77 Knicks.

46:11.070 --> 46:14.744
You think your fucking Earl 'The Pearl,'
could play John Starks?

46:14.805 --> 46:17.573
Hey, man, Earl 'The Pearl'
would've blown fucking John Starks

46:17.656 --> 46:19.616
right out of the Garden, my friend.

46:19.677 --> 46:22.226
John Starks would take Earl 'The Pearl...'

46:22.414 --> 46:23.442
Annie,

46:24.121 --> 46:25.264
I'd like you to meet Rodney.

46:25.325 --> 46:27.084
Rodney, this is my friend, Annie.

46:27.199 --> 46:29.687
Your girl is a fucking knock-out.

46:29.898 --> 46:32.097
Rodney, here, is about
a half a gallon of sewage

46:32.158 --> 46:33.657
that just backed up
from New York City, Annie.

46:33.718 --> 46:35.689
Hey, don't give me that shit!

46:36.742 --> 46:38.117
